article.headline: Providence 76, Rutgers 50
article.story: PROVIDENCE, R.I. (AP) -- Brian McKenzie scored a career-high 24 points on 10-of-14 shooting as Providence raced to an easy 76-50 victory over Rutgers for its first league win Wednesday night. Geoff McDermott scored seven points and added game-high totals of eight rebounds and eight assists for the Friars (10-5, 1-2 Big East). JR Inman was high scorer for Rutgers (8-8, 0-3 Big East) with 11 points as the Scarlet Knights dropped their third game in a row. The Friars held the Scarlet Knights to just two field goals on 20 attempts in the second half. Rutgers shot just 32 percent for the game on 14-of-44 shooting. Providence also outscored Rutgers in the paint, 44-14. They scored 23 points off 18 Rutgers turnovers. The first half featured five lead changes and one tie. An Inman layup put Rutgers ahead, 16-9, then Providence regained the lead, 17-16 on two McDermott free throws. Providence led 35-34 at the half and continued to surge ahead with Rutgers unable to make a field goal for almost 12 minutes during one stretch. A McKenzie drive put Providence ahead, 76-46 with 3:31 to go.
